description: The adventures of the new crew of theÂ EnterpriseÂ continue in this all new two-part story that takes place soon after the events of the last film! While Vulcans struggle to survive in the wake of their homeworld's destruction at the hands of rogue Romulans, and some Vulcans believe that the logical response can be summed up in one word: revenge! STAR TREK writer/producer Roberto Orci oversees this original story set in the timeline leading up to the blockbuster film sequel!Â
name: Vulcan's Vengeance, Part 1

description:
NEW CREATIVE TEAM! BOLD NEW DIRECTION!

"THE CRACK IN EVERYTHING", PART 1

Hot on the heels of THE DARKNESS II video game release, Top Cow proudly welcomes the new creative team of DAVID HINE (THE DARKNESS: FOUR HORSEMEN, THE BULLETPROOF COFFIN) and JEREMY HAUN (ARTIFACTS, BATTLE HYMN, Detective Comics)! On the surface, Jackie Estacado has everything he ever wanted - control of the Darkness, a successful career, and happy family life. Only his desire to make his life truly perfect will be his undoing.
name: The Crack In Everything, Part One

And who, exactly, is responsible for the mysterious pure white helicopters and their crews? With the country suffering a new revolution and the Government having lost control, Murphy will discover the truth behind the new America. And back in Old Detroit, the final fate of OCP will be revealed.

Em finds herself stranded in the Everlands with no way home, with no one but a lost little girl to guide her. Together, the two make their way across the âStolen Moments,â encountering people and places that have been forgotten by history, or remembered only as stories. But with the Shadows and an army of living statues dogging her heels, and even greater dangers ahead, can Em survive long enough to find a way back to the only life she knows?

When the Lawgiver was assassinated by a human freedom fighter, the world plunged into chaos. Sullivan, now free from Alayaâs clutches, takes humanityâs fight for freedom to the next level, in a devastating gambit for ape and human alike! Writer Daryl Gregory and artist Carlos Magno continue their critically acclaimed run and end this arc on a cliffhanger that you have to read to believe!
name: Children of Fire, Part 4

description:
The Return of the Swamp Witch

Big Weird battles Muscus Man as he escapes Vampuh. The Swamp Witch tries to become Weird Melvin's greatest fan as we hear the origin of Shag.
name: The Return of the Swamp Witch

description:
The controversial cartoonist Rory Hayes was a self-taught dynamo of the underground comics revolution. Attracting equal parts derision and praise (the latter from the likes of R. Crumb and Bill Griffith), Hayes emerged as comicsâ great primitive, drawing horror comics in a genuinely horrifying and hallucinatory manner (some have called him the Fletcher Hanks of the underground). He has influenced a generation of cartoonists, from RAW to Fort Thunder and back again.

This book, the first retrospective of Hayesâ career ever published, features the best of his underground comics output alongside paintings, covers, and artifacts rarely seen by human eyes â as well as astounding, previously unprinted comics from his teenage years and movie posters for his numerous homemade films. The Art and Comix of Rory Hayes also serves as a biography and critique with a memoir of growing up with Rory by his brother, the illustrator Geoffrey Hayes, and a career-spanning essay by Edwin Pouncey (a.k.a. Savage Pencil). Also included is a rare interview with Hayes himself.

description: Aqualad visits Atlantis with Superboy and Miss Martian. But can they stop an insidious new menace that threatens to plunge the undersea kingdom into civil war?
name: Under The Surface...

description: Itâs all been building up to this. Captain Kirk, Cosmic Boy, and the rest of the timelost Legionnaires and Starfleet officers have reached the end of the line, and are confronted with the powerful forces which have unwritten their respective histories. But with half of their teams stranded in the past and the other half held prisoner in the future, what chance do they have of overcoming the odds and restoring the worlds they once knew?
name: Part Six

description: The amazing Mike Choi (X-Force) contributes a sequence in the latest chapter of the miniseries that has everyone talking! The jaw-dropping twists continue, as true intentions come to light, enemies and allies thought long gone return, and the death toll continues to riseâ¦Plus, the start of a two-part backup story starring the all-new Undersea Agent on a deadly solo mission!
name: At Breath's End; Aqualung

description: In this awesome 50th issue, questions are answered! Mysteries are solved! The Tiny Titans may be one step closer to becoming Super Heroes! This issue may change your life! Plus, it's highly recommended by Franco's mom!

After seriously injuring an opponent in a boxing match-Sohei quits his dream of ever being a pro boxer. Ten years later, after a string of failed jobs and relationships, his friend Chika finally convinces him to get back into boxing. But where Sohei was once champ material, he is now 25 years old (over the hill in boxing years) and must play catch up with all the 18-year-olds at the gym. To make things worse, Chikaâs been secretly in love with Sohei for years, and has about had it with waiting for Sohei to figure it out.â¯With his upcoming pro test, his squabbles with the youngsters in the boxing club, and Chikaâs increasingly bold advances, will Sohei finally find some direction and happiness in his life?
name: Vol. 1

description: After receiving an interesting phone call from his brother, Tatsuki Hiroshi decides to go for a visit. There he encounters Miura, and as the two get to know each other,they begin dating. It is not supposed to be for anything but fun with no strings attached. So when did Tatsuki become a fool for love? What is he to do?! As he finds out, affairs of the heart are complicated!
name: Liar In Love; Liar Learning Love

description: Kojimaâs friendly attitude and upbeat, playful innocence help to guarantee his status as a well-liked boy. But the brooding Nakahara is the exact opposite! A shy wallflower, he seems aloof and is constantly alone...until Kojima suddenly steps into his dark, painful world. When the time comes to take flight, will the two boys simply escape to a fantasy free of pain and suffering, or can they break out and soar into a bright, exciting future of their own?
name: Vol. 1

description: Bright Kojima and sullen Nakahara are so much more than typical school pals. Kojimaâs home serves as both a safe-haven and a fun escape for his deeply troubled friend. When a family feud threatens to rip apart Nakaharaâs world piece-by-piece, Kojima steps in to protect his heartâs companion. Sadly, some lies have a secret history older than the young boys. Now more than ever, their future happiness hangs in the balance of an old feudâs resolution!
name: Vol. 2

description: Nakaharaâs family is slowly falling apart.â¯ Heâs forced to watch while his sick mother battles twisted memories and fits of amnesia...and itâs keeping him away from his heartâs true desire.â¯Caring Kojima wants nothing more than to share the burden with his trusted friend, but with exams and graduation looming larger than ever, heâs got his own future to worry about.â¯ Itâs a pass-or-fail fight to the finish!â¯ Can the boys rely on the strength of their loyalty, or will graduation mark the end of their time together?
name: Vol. 3

description: Kojimaâs friendly attitude and upbeat, playful innocence help to guarantee his status as a well-liked boy. But the brooding Nakahara is the exact opposite! A shy wallflower, he seems aloof and is constantly alone...until Kojima suddenly steps into his dark, painful world. When the time comes to take flight, will the two boys simply escape to a fantasy free of pain and suffering, or can they break out and soar into a bright, exciting future of their own? Little Butterfly spreads its wings and sets off on a flight path full of love, longing and plenty of tender moments. Even the smallest of creatures dreams of soaring beyond the mundane world! The best selling DMP series is back by popular demand, and in a one-volume limited edition omnibus!
name: Vol. 1-3

description: A shy and clumsy university student; a salary man trapped in an arranged marriage; a not-so-skilled novice magician; two high school boys who have been fighting it out since they were kids; and a humanoid dogâ¦ what could they possibly have in common? Well, theyâre about to find love in the most unexpected of places. Oh, and thereâs another thing about them as well â they all seem to cry over the simplest of things. Experience loveâs first joy and heartache in this collection of light-hearted stories.
name: Vol. 1

description: Yasuie runs the Kiryuuin Detective Agency in Tokyoâs Shinjuku Nichome neighborhood. With no clients and no money, itâs a constant struggle just to live and pay the rent. For the past seven years, Yasuieâs assistant and partner Yoshiyuki has been willing to suffer through all the good and bad times with him â even considering Yasuieâs playful advances, which approach sexual harassment â but life has a way of changing things. Faced with his familyâs ultimatum, Yoshiyuki must choose between a penniless future with Yasuie and a more traditional lifestyle. Can Yasuie convince Yoshiyuki to stay with him? Even if Yasuie does confess the true reason he brought Yoshiyuki into the detective business, will it be enough to change his partnerâs mind?
name: Vol. 1

description: Sent by the Lost Boys to find them a father, the impish Air settles upon the first open window he could find. The window happens to be Mizukiâs, who is forcibly whisked away to Neverland. Finding out that he is now supposed to play âfatherâ to the Lost Boys, Mizuki is incensed. However, forced to stay put, he gets to know the Lost Boys â and Air â a little better. Perhaps a little too well as Mizuki finds that he is helplessly falling in love with the boy.Staying true to the boysâ love genre, readers will find Lost Boysâ soft and sensitive storyline to be quite a delightful surprise. This is Peter Panâ¦yaoi style!
name: Vol. 1

description: Have you ever daydreamed about the quiet, handsome guy at the train station?â¯ How about the awkward boy who works at the corner boutique... or that college crush who now works in your office? â¯The world is filled with men who are fuel for fantasy, and Love Bus Stop is a non-stop ride down streets made for illicit crushes, secret love affairs and quiet bedroom trysts. â¯Let your mind wander, and your body will surely follow...
name: Vol. 1

description: We first met superstar actor Koji Mizuhara and rising pop idol Kyo Ayukawa in âJunior Escort,â where a passionate misunderstanding led to true love. Now, the âSweet Slave Scandalâ series continues in this second installment, âLove Code.â Despite their hectic schedules, Mizuhara and Ayukawa still manage to keep their relationship happy and lovey-dovey. The future of their careers seems bright as well. Mizuhara is about to make his Hollywood debut and Ayukawa is about to record a music CD. But Mizuharaâs dark past and some jealous people will try to break this couple apart. And, in the end, Ayukawa needs to decide which is more importantâhis career or Mizuhara.
name: Vol. 1

description: Pride and ego are the first to go in a relationship, they say. But pride is what talented interior designer Kei Yamashiro has in abundance, while ego is what his client, Takashi Okumura, has more than enough of. Will they ever get along? Itâs control freak Yamashiro versus control freak Okumura. Will one back down and relinquish Love Control?
name: Vol. 1

description: Okumura, the director, and Yamashiro, the designer, have finally graduated from flirtation to romance. Only they wonât admit it. The two are too proud to express feelings of love and affection. But when a third wheel â a brash and handsome bartender named Sasatani â shows up and boldly states his intention to court Yamashiro, will Okumura finally admit his love to Yamashiro? And will Yamashiro admit to loving him back?
name: Vol. 2

description: Keigo Someha, a private detective and assassin, finds himself nursing Emiya Nozaki-who had an unbelievable, near-death experience right in front of his-back to health. Emiya knows virtually nothing about sex and everyday life, thus Keigo feels that it is essential to shield him from the world's perversions. Meanwhile, Hamuro becomes fixated when he discovers Emiya's unique power, and he cunningly lures Emiya into a research institute! Will Keigo's powers be strong enough to tear Emiya back from Hamuro's cruel grip?
name: Vol. 1

description: Mild-mannered math teacher, Shirai, always sees a certain kid at detention--Akagi, who also happens to be a popular actor. For some reason, Akagi seems to be a bit too friendly and he keeps whispering to Shirai that heâs cute! Itâs hard to tell if Akagi is being serious or not. But one fateful day, when they are in an empty classroom, Akagi makes his move. He seems serious this time! Shirai resists, and pushes him away. Before he can figure out whatâs going on, Akagi suddenly drops out of school... leaving Shirai more confused than ever!
name: Vol. 1

description: Will the young teacher Yuuri ever know what it feels like to be in love? After all, he's the unlucky inheritor of a pheromone that makes him 100% irresistible to every man (and woman) who crosses his path! It's too bad that the stubborn and handsome student Hasegawa seems totally unfazed by Yuuri's frustrating situation. In fact, Hasegawa is convinced that the two men will someday marry! It's up to Yuuri to figure out whether the boy's heart is in the right place. Has the lovestruck Hasegawa simply fallen prey to the passion-inducing power of a family curse?
name: Vol. 1

description: Tomonori Ozawa has just landed his dream job at a large publishing firm. The only catch is, he is the new editor of a Boyâs Love magazine! With that, comes the responsibility of managing Sakurako Kakyoin, a male yaoi artist who is notorious for missing his deadlines. To become a fullâfledged editor, Tomonori-kun has to start from the bottom â checking drafts, editing scripts and lettering. Now if only Kakyoin-sensei would stop sexually harassing him, he could actually get some work done!
name: Vol. 1

description: Day after day, young manga editor Tomonori Ozawa slaves over the steamy scripts that make Boys Love the hottest magazine on the rack. But one-shot stories and office gossip arenât the only things on Ozawaâs mind.â¯ When the talented yaoi creator Sakurako Kakyoin steps up the pressure both at work and after hours, Ozawa must decide whether to keep their relationship professional or punch the clock for overtime! And will a mysterious new artist only spell trouble for these secret lovers?
name: Vol. 2

description: Level-headed Kazushi never wanted his life taken over by the likes of gorgeous Izumi! But then again, who could possibly resist such a charming flirt? After endless days and nights of passion, their future together seems certain...or is it? When Izumi receives a strange phone call, it's up to Kazushi to both find his vanished lover and solve a lingering mystery. Can these two men share a love that lasts, or will it tear them both apart?
name: Vol. 1

description: When salaryman Asada loses a transfer, he tries to drink away his sorrows. After passing out on the side of a road, he is found by Nao, a young baker, who is trying to revitalize his father's bakery. As Asada helps Nao resurrect the bakery, he finds himself falling for him-but unable to admit his feelings, he decides to end their friendship. Three years later, Asada finds himself in need of Nao's help. Will Nao be able to forgive Asada?
name: Vol. 1

description: Shinoda and Serizawa are so close that when Serizawa suddenly needs to find a place to crash for a little while, Shinoda opens the door to his beautiful apartment without a momentâs hesitationâ¦but thereâs a catch! Will a kiss every morning change the way these two college pals feel about one another? And is there any way to guarantee that you wonât destroy a friendship once your feelings blossom into something new?
name: Vol. 1

description: Welcome to Sakurajo High, home to some of the most privileged boys in Japan! Koji's mother just married up in the world and now this average boy is finding it hard to adjust to a school where nearly all of his peers have grown up wealthy. Meanwhile, Taiki is a playboy who insists that he doesn't want to go steady...until he meets the adorable rent-a-boy, Makoto! Love Training follows the lives of different students as they find out what itâs like to attend a school full of beautiful boys! Where one story ends, another begins.
name: Vol. 1

description: Rei is a president of student councilâhe is always so cool and well-mannered, impressing everyone with a perfect attendance record. One day, Shindo, a transfer student with outstanding grades, comes to school and starts to have a crush on him. During the semester, Shindo begins making moves on Rei, and really begins to falls in love with him. Shindo is outgoing and sociable. Rei is reserved and a bit snobbish. A perfect scenario of opposites attracts...or do they?
name: Vol. 1

description:
Don't miss this Green Lantern volume collecting HAL JORDAN #1-3, ABIN SUR #1- 3, FRANKENSTEIN AND THE CREATURES OF THE UNKNOWN #1-3 and GREEN ARROW INDUSTRIES #1. Not a dream, not an imaginary story, not an elseworld. This is Flash Fact: When Barry Allen wakes at his desk, he discovers the world has changed. Family is alive, loved ones are strangers, and close friends are different, gone or worse. It's a world on the brink of a cataclysmic war â but where are Earth's Greatest Heroes to stop it?

Back Blurb

HE SURVIVED THE CRASH!

Flashpoint has changed the DC Universe, and nothing is as it was before. Now, Abin Sur never died, and Hal Jordan never became the Green Lantern of Sector 2814. Earth has yet to be dragged into the Blackest Night, but a new horror awaits it...a war between Atlantis and the Amazons that threaten to destroy the world---and the Life Entity that dwells within it.

In his mission to protect all life, Abin will defy the Guardians of the Universe and stand with Earth's heroes to fight Wonder Woman and Aquaman and end the war, but to embrace his destiny he'll have to battle his best friend: the Green Lantern Sinestro. And though he's not a Lantern in this world, Captain Hal Jordan will become a true hero when he flies a mission that has potential to turn the tide of the war...and to be his last. Told by ADAM SCHLAGMAN (UNTOLD TALES OF BLACKEST NIGHT) in the interwining miniseries ABIN SUR: THE GREEN LANTERN and HAL JORDAN with art from FELIPE MASSAFERA (GREEN LANTERN: EMERALD WARRIORS) and CLIFF RICHARDS (TITANS).

Oliver Queen will struggle to find the hero inside when a mysterious assailant attacks GREEN ARROW INDUSTRIES, and acclaimed writer JEFF LEMIRE (ANIMAL MAN) shows in FRANKENSTEIN AND THE CREATURES OF THE UNKNOWN that in a strange world like this, the strangest heroes may be the greatest heroes. Frank and his Creature Commandos on World War II for the Allies...can they turn the tide in this war, as well?

Before the DC UNIVERSE changes forever, experience a world like you never have before...THE WORLD OF FLASHPOINT!
name: TPB

volume.name: Flashpoint: The World of Flashpoint Featuring Green Lantern

description:
Don't miss this Flash volume collecting GRODD OF WAR #1, KID FLASH LOST #1-3, LEGION OF DOOM #1-3, REVERSE FLASH #1 and CITIZEN COLD #1-3. Not a dream, not an imaginary story, not an elseworld. This is Flash Fact: When Barry Allen wakes at his desk, he discovers the world has changed. Family is alive, loved ones are strangers, and close friends are different, gone or worse. It's a world on the brink of a cataclysmic war â but where are Earth's Greatest Heroes to stop it?

Back Blurb

WHATEVER HAPPENED TO THE WORLD'S GREATEST SUPERVILLAINS?

Flashpoint changed the DC Universe, and nothing is as it was before. Now, the Flash has never become the hero he was meant to be, and those closes to him feel the greatest effects of the timestorm enveloping the entire universe.

Now, Central City's greatest hero is the mysterious CITIZEN COLD, from writer/artist SCOTT KOLINS (THE FLASH). But as Cold's enemies in the Rogues seek vengeance on him, can he keep his long-hidden past a secret?

Now---his evil unchecked by the Flash---GORILLA GRODD could conquer an entire continent, and in LEGION OF DOOM written by ADAM GLASS (SUICIDE SQUAD), Heatwawe takes over the world's most secure prison---with the world's most dangerous inside of it.

And in KID FLASH by STERLING GATES (HAWK AND DOVE), Bart Allen will find himself adrift in time, the only one who can stop the storm threatening to engulf of all of reality...a storm possibly cause by the machinations of REVERSE FLASH!

Before the DC Universe changes forever, experience a world like you never have before...THE WORLD OF FLASHPOINT!
name: TPB

volume.name: Flashpoint: The World of Flashpoint Featuring The Flash

description: Nishioka is a reckless up-and-coming photographer who prides himself on his independence. Matsukawa is a very rich and successful supervisor at a major advertising company and the object of every womanâs desire. In fact, Matsukawa seems to get along with just about everyone except Nishioka â yet every time the two team up for a modeling contract, their project is a smash hit. On the surface, Matsukawa and Nishioka butt heads at every turn. So why does Nishioka secretly take pictures of Matsukawa when he thinks no one is looking?
name: Vol. 1

description: Last time, Nishioka and Matsukawa appeared to be on their way to love, but the rivalries, pressures and time demands that come with normal relationships can quickly get out of hand when you mix business and pleasure. Soon, Matsukawa finds his agency responsibilities are pulling him away from the object of his affection, leaving Nishioka less than enthusiastic about his own work. If Nishioka canât find the words to say how he truly feels, does he risk losing Matsukawa for good?!
name: Vol. 2

description: A bit of Christmas merriment leads Kouno to a night of passion with his friend and secret crush, Natsu. Come morning, the two are left to deal with their hangovers and an awkward situation. Can sleeping with your best friend lead to a deep connection of love, or is it a sure-fire way to ruin a relationship for good?
name: Vol. 1

description: Kazuto loves being the life of the party...even when he canât remember his wild night once the sun rises! But whoâs this strange man curled up in his bed?! It turns out that the scrappy Kazuto has been purchased by the suave and successful Takasugi for an entire month. Everyone knows that you shouldnât mix business with pleasure, but these two men will have a hard time playing by the rules if they let their bodies take control!
name: Vol. 1

description: Gazing through his office window, design entrepreneur Kazumi is struck by the handsome figure of Yajima - a younger businessman who works in the opposite building. Such captivating scenery certainly does make the day go by faster! When a chance encounter brings the two together, Kazumi quickly finds himself in a whirl-wind of deep emotion and powerful desire. Can a workaholic like Kazumi find time to give all of himself to his new love? Exactly how is it Yajima seems to know everything about Kazumi from the moment they first meet? Is it his simple magic trick, or does Yajimaâs kind demeanor hide some secret possessiveness?
name: Vol. 1

description: It is the mid-19th century, and a remarkably beautiful 18-year-old has been crowned King Ludwig II of Bavariaâ¦ In the midst of a confrontation with Prussia and Austria, Ludwig II retreats from reality into an exquisite world colored by the music of Wagner. Will he be rescued from this world of fantasy and madness or can he continue living this way?
name: Vol. 1

description: The kingdom of Bavaria was absorbed into the German Empire during the latter half of the 19th century. The stunningly handsome king of Bavariaâ who never married and who would have operas and plays privately staged for himâwandered between fantasy and reality, alone in his extravagant crystal palace, Neuschwanstein. âI want to remain an eternal mystery to myself and others,â Ludwig II once said, and now we reach the final act of his drama.
name: Vol. 2

description: Two soldiers from warring countries are bound by a pledge as master and servant. Taki Reizen is a Commander of sublime beauty, shouldering the fate of his nation. Called âMad Dogâ because of his rough temperament, Klaus has sworn his loyalty to him as a knight. Despite this, those around them are cold and disapproving, full of various misgivings. For all their genuine feelings, what will come of love made cruel by the violence of war?
name: Vol. 1

description: When a mysterious train charts a path through the demilitarized (and allegedly tainted) No-Man's-Land, Taki must act quickly in order to prevent its passage into his domain. But will he protect his own boundaries from the brute advances of Claus...or is he prepared to welcome a forceful invasion? Sometimes a minor skirmish becomes an all-out war for prized territory...and only the strongest soldier will be left standing once the final shot is fired.
name: Vol. 2

description: Mamiya is the seemingly aloof owner and master of the mysterious "Mamiya Doll House", a store that can make your every dream come true with its perfectly lifelike Bioroids. But what will cool Mamiya do when faced with Kobayashi, a persistent young man who has fallen hard for him, and is the type to never give up once he's set his sights on something?! Follow the story of Mamiya and Kobayashi, and the dolls and their masters, and 32-pages never before collected! Take an excursion into the world of living dolls from creator Kazuhiko Mishima, "First Stage of Love" and "You Make My Head Spin"!
name: Vol. 1

description: In the heart of New York City, florist Dan âDiamondâ Loving makes his living selling colorful bouquets to customers looking for a little romance in their lives. Actually, Dan has a romance of his own â a secretive affair with handsome, powerful CEO, Rock Melville. Rock owns a good part of the city, including Danâs own flower shop, and the business responsibilities which go with that make him a hard man to get to. For some, money and power can be a powerful aphrodisiac, but for Dan, dealing with a workaholic boyfriend has its difficulties. True, the time he does spend with Rock always warms Danâs heart, but what good is a lover he can only see once in a while? Is Dan destined to always come last in Rockâs busy schedule? Or will Rock make the commitment necessary to keep their love alive?
name: Vol. 1

description: Seventeen-year-old Maki enrolls in a summer class to learn math and...experience sex for the first time?! A source of amusement at first, their encounters soon turn into an intimate affair for Maki. Wanting to know more about his hot tutor Haruji, Maki soon discovers that the teacher is still hung up over Mizuguchi, an instructor Haruji himself had an affair with. Now, Mizuguchi is actually an English teacher at Makiâs high school. Plus, he also happens to be the one Maki has a crush on!
name: Vol. 1
